I’ve dined at Casa Del Mar and placed orders on seamless and uber East many many many times. I don’t eat shrimp and they usually have no problem substituting salmon when I request it with my orders. Have done so manyyyyyy times dining or ordering delivery. However, today the young lady I spoke with gave me a bit of a hard time and seemed confused my request.  First she told me I would have to cancel my order, order a salmon entree dish and note that I wanted a salad... WHAT? By the time she told me that their restaurant was closed in the app so that wasn’t even possible. I told her I have no problem paying an additional charge even though they’ve never asked me to pay more before. It wasn’t an issue until she told me I would have to pay an extra $10 for salmon to be added to the salad I ordered... $10 on top of the additional $8 I already paid to add on a protein to my meal. I asked several times just to make sure she was really trying to charge me a total of $29 for a salmon Cesar salad and she was! Absolutely ridiculous.  They’ve definitely lost a loyal customer. Honestly, I’m so turned off by the whole exchange that I’d never order or dine there again.

I wanted to try this place since they first opened so my cousin and I went for our birthday. The ambiance is nice and that's as far as it goes. The food was ok but lacked flavor, and my fish had scales. There was no seasoning on the vegetables and the mashed potato was more like smashed baked potato. The service was not the best but it wasn't bad either so I tipped the server $20. I looked at my receipt the following day (because we had finished celebrating after dinner) and I saw that the server had already added a 15% tip which made her total in tips $37. I won't be going back.

I was aware from closely reading their website that they add a 15% gratuity to all bills, but was surprised to find that when I received my receipt from the bar they had elected to add 18% to the first receipt you are given, but have just a normal tip line on the receipt you sign with the already inflated bill that people unknowingly tip on. I watched a number of customers order a bottle of Stella and pay cash, $10, unaware that this already includes the tip then be encouraged to utilize the large tip jar sitting on the counter. There’s no indication anywhere in the restaurant that this is the practice, just on the website. Just seems like a deceptive business practice.

I recently took my family to this Fabulous Restaurant to celebrate my daughter graduation,for this happy occasion I couldn’t have pick a better restaurant. He then took our drink order on a very timely manner including a nice bottle of pinogrillo he offer us some appetizers like fried calamari  and clams casino These are the best clams I Had ever so flavorful they are a must have when you come here, we weren’t ready to order our food yet so he when on to his other tables . Ralph Soon came back, we ask some questions about some of the great dishes that are in the menu he was very knowledgeable and we where all very happy with his recommendations. My son in-law ha d a  skirt stake which was beautifully decorated and properly cooked medium  and very juicy I felt in love with my trifongo that is made with green plantains Maduros and Yuca served with churasco on the side my Wyfe had the grilled salmon that was so good tender juicy and substantial that we all tasted it. My daughter had the Brest of stuffed chicken which she enjoyed very much . I love the the Freshness specially of the seafood because of the fact that the Restaurant also has its own sea food market in the same premises. The dining room is spacious very modern and beautifully decorated it is a great place to visit I have being in the restaurant business for more than thirty five years and I highly recommend Casa Del Mar
